# Fixture (i): nonlinear TC, both-atoms-change-in-one-batch crossings.
#
# Batch 1: seed a 4-node chain 1->2->3->4. p ends up:
#   {(1,2),(2,3),(3,4),(1,3),(2,4),(1,4)}
#   p(1,4) has TWO derivations: p(1,3),edge(3,4) is a base-joined... no,
#   both p(1,3) and p(3,4)-via-p are p-atoms; p(1,4) is derivable as
#   p(1,Y=2),p(2,4) AND p(1,Y=3),p(3,4) -- a genuine double-derivation
#   (two distinct same-stratum join instances landing on the same head
#   row), which is the exactly-once stress: C_r for p(1,4) must reach the
#   correct MULTIPLICITY (2 distinct rule instances), not merely presence.
#
# Batch 2 (BOTH-DELETED crossing): remove edge(2,3) AND edge(3,4) in the
# same batch. This removes the base support for p(2,3), p(3,4) AND every
# multi-hop p row through node 3. Two DIFFERENT same-stratum p rows
# (p(2,3) and p(3,4)) are claimed into the overdelete set in the same
# batch -- possibly the same claim round -- stressing Delta_D discipline:
# a wrong resolution (firing over the raw drained queue instead of the
# per-round claimed frontier, or using InNew instead of
# SurvivesSoFar/AliveAtClaim for the OTHER position) either double-fires
# the removal of p(1,4) via TWO different join instances (driving C_r
# negative -> commit assert) or under/over-removes p(1,3)/p(2,4).
#
# Batch 3 (BOTH-ADDED crossing): add edge(4,5) AND edge(5,6) in the same
# batch, onto surviving chain 1->2 (edge(2,3)/(3,4) are gone). This
# creates a fresh 2-hop extension in one batch: p(4,6) is derivable only
# by COMBINING the two just-added same-stratum p rows p(4,5) and p(5,6)
# in the SAME round -- the canonical same-round double-claim-then-join
# case FLAG-F/H is about. A wrong InNewWithFrontier (if it meant
# "claimed-this-round only" per FLAG-F reading (ii)) would make this
# instance FAIL to fire (since both sides are freshly claimed this exact
# round and reading "InNewWithFrontier=InNew" is required for the
# earlier-position side to see the later side as already new).
#
# Batch 4 (ONE-ADDED-ONE-DELETED crossing): remove edge(1,2) AND add
# edge(6,7) in the same batch. Unrelated ends of the graph change
# polarity in one batch; stresses that OVERDELETE and INSERT phases for
# the SAME stratum in the SAME epoch do not cross-contaminate each
# other's claimed-frontier state (kDelNow/kAddNow must not leak across
# phases).
batch
+ add_edge 1 2
+ add_edge 2 3
+ add_edge 3 4
end

batch
- add_edge 2 3
- add_edge 3 4
end

batch
+ add_edge 4 5
+ add_edge 5 6
end

batch
- add_edge 1 2
+ add_edge 6 7
end
